Description:

Are you looking for a low maintenance lifestyle without the disadvantages of a unit complex? Or are you looking for an affordable, great returning investment property? If so contact us today, this one will sell quickly!

An original cottage, a sizable yard with a shared driveway! A near new unit to the rear.

Description:
Auction This Saturday!
This unique home has a feel that can't be replicated and is sure to wow all who inspect. With soaring ceilings, exposed timber and timeless appeal makes this large home well suited to all families, couples, holiday makers and anyone after that ideal place to call home. Comprising: 4 bedrooms with ensuite off master, open plan kitchen, meals and lounge, upstairs retreat, central bathroom, side drive to genuine 4 car garage with bathroom/huge workshop, landscaped garden and a rear studio that could be used for art, teenagers retreat or bedroom. Special features include: solar panels, claw foot bath, wood fire heater in shed, gas log fire in the house, a unique open plan design, loads of natural light with an outdoor aspect from every room and a classic mud brick finish. Close to public transport, local shops & schools, minutes drive to Somers beach and some of the Peninsula's leading wineries and great freeway access for a short trip to town. A must see!

Description:
FINISH WITH FLAIR AND REAP THE REWARDS!
An exciting work in progress with some significant big ticket items already crossed off the `to do' list, this value-for-money two-bedroom with study home is packed to the rafters with potential, representing budget-friendly coastal buying at its best.
So whether you're keen to roll up your sleeves and reap the rewards or call in a few favours from your tradie mates, it's all about the finishing touches and tweaking the layout for a perfect fit.
So what's on offer? Starting from the ground up you're looking at a lovely level 806sqm block so there's plenty of scope to extend the footprint, add a large garage or just let the kids and pets roam free.
Inside, open-plan family living and dining feels light and airy under a soaring raked ceiling with exposed beams and trusses, while sliding doors create an easy link with a large semi-enclosed barbecue deck, overlooking the beautifully landscaped gardens, complete with cafe blinds to extend the season.
Incorporated into the the space, the large modern kitchen with plenty of storage is almost complete and comes pre-equipped with a 900mm under bench oven, 900mm gas cooktop with wok burner and huge island bench with stainless steel dishwasher.
The current layout provides two bedrooms, both with robe storage, a wet room bathroom and a bonus study/office (or extra bedroom) with separate entrance, but the future here is limited only by your imagination.
Just two minutes walk to the Crib Point shops and well-serviced by public transport, extras include reverse-cycle airconditioning, a handy garden shed, 10,000 litres of water tanks and off street parking.
Property Features:
- 806sqm* block
- 15 squares* of living
- Partially renovated 2 bedroom home with study/home office or 3rd bedroom
- Roll up your sleeves and reap the rewards
- Two minutes' walk to local shops
- Close to trains and bus stop
- Open-plan family living and dining
- Raked ceiling, exposed beams & trusses
- Large modern kitchen with stainless steel appliances
- Covered outdoor entertaining deck
- Solar Panels
- Bright family bathroom
- Reverse-cycle airconditioning
- 10,000* litres of water tanks
- High fences surrounding private back yard
- Landscaped gardens
- Handy garden shed
- Off street parking
* all measurements and dimensions are approximate.
Contact Brad Boyd 0434 260 655
